lead_paragraph: Tax collectors in Atlantic City, New Jersey, garnered bids for less than half of the tax liens on bankrupt casinos they had hoped to auction on Thursday, another blow to the city's already weak coffers.

headline.main: Some Atlantic City, N.J., Casino Tax Liens Fail to Draw Bidders
